{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01ERENKDKqbJcSKRJkBk8ZTB","type":"tool_result","content":"36-2. **A single adversarial verification pass** against the final built artifact. No per-story micro-verification. No session flags. No proof document regex parsing. One blind evaluator agent — no source code access, only Docker, observability, and documentation — exercises the final artifact subjectively and produces a structured JSON verdict. The evaluator reads ACs in user language and independently figures out how to test them.\n37-\n38:3. **A multi-level agent and workflow configuration system.** Agents and workflows exist at three levels: embedded (ships with codeharness), user-level, and project-level — with hybrid patching to customize without replacing. 9 embedded agents (8 BMAD + evaluator) and 1 default workflow ship out of the box. Agent personality uses BMAD-compatible fields as the base with optional PersonaNexus-compatible traits for fine-grained behavioral tuning.\n39-\n40-BMAD owns planning (briefs, PRDs, architecture, stories). Codeharness owns execution and verification — taking BMAD's output and driving it to a proven-working artifact.\n--\n60-### User Success\n61-\n62:- User runs `codeharness run` with the default workflow — all stories execute through assigned agents without human intervention\n63-- The blind evaluator exercises the final artifact and produces a pass/fail verdict the user trusts\n64-- Workflow YAML is understandable in under 5 minutes\n--\n107-9. Multi-level agent configuration (embedded/user/project) with hybrid patching\n108-10. Multi-level workflow configuration (embedded/user/project) with hybrid patching\n109:11. 9 embedded agents (8 BMAD + evaluator) and 1 default embedded workflow\n110-12. Issue tracking via `issues.yaml` — replaces beads, retro findings auto-added, engine executes issues alongside stories\n111-13. Legacy deletion (Ralph bash, session flags, proof parsers, self-verify hooks, beads)\n--\n114-### Growth (Phase 2)\n115-\n116:- Multiple default workflow templates (web app, CLI, library)\n117-- Evaluator prompt tuning based on logged evaluator decisions\n118-- Pluggable evaluator strategies (Playwright MCP for web apps, API exerciser for backends, CLI runner for tools)\n--\n155-### Journey 3: Agent & Workflow Customization\n156-\n157:New project — React frontend. Alex patches the default workflow and the dev agent at project level:\n158-\n159-```yaml\n--\n254-- Formally specified with a JSON schema\n255-- Validatable via `codeharness validate`\n256:- Self-documenting — the default workflow is the best documentation\n257-\n258-Key schema elements:\n--\n307-npm install -g codeharness\n308-claude plugin install codeharness\n309:codeharness init    # detect stack, generate default workflow\n310-codeharness run     # execute\n311-```\n--\n332-- FR4: User can define loop steps in the flow using a `loop:` block containing an ordered list of tasks to repeat\n333-- FR5: System validates workflow YAML against a JSON schema at parse time and rejects malformed definitions\n334:- FR6: System ships a default embedded workflow that handles standard BMAD sprint execution without user customization\n335-\n336-### Agent Configuration\n--\n396-### CLI Commands\n397-\n398:- FR43: User can run `codeharness init` to detect stack, generate default workflow, and set up the project\n399-- FR44: User can run `codeharness run` to execute the workflow\n400-- FR45: User can run `codeharness validate` to check workflow and agent YAML against schemas\n--\n419-### Reliability\n420-\n421:- NFR6: Engine state survives process crashes — on restart, execution resumes from the last completed task\n422-- NFR7: Evaluator session timeout does not crash the engine — timeout is a scored failure, not a fatal error\n423-- NFR8: All engine state is persisted to disk after each task completion"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_017HxP1cbYsBpSzeobjawugj","session_id":"655665ef-6468-4ba6-a46a-b395b1530cdd","uuid":"3873194c-28d9-4af9-8a1e-dbdf492db026","timestamp":"2026-04-02T11:46:30.581Z"}
